Field.Name: Account
Field.Description: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

Field.Name: AdvId
Field.Description: Unique identifier of advertisement message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AdvSide
Field.Description: Broker's side of advertised trade

Field.Name: AdvTransType
Field.Description: Identifies advertisement message transaction type

Field.Name: AvgPx
Field.Description: Calculated average price of all fills on this order. For Fixed Income trades AvgPx is always expressed as percent-of-par, regardless of the PriceType (423) of LastPx (3). I.e., AvgPx will contain an average of percent-of-par values (see LastParPx (669)) for issues traded in Yield, Spread or Discount.

Field.Name: BeginSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

Field.Name: BeginString
Field.Description: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: BodyLength
Field.Description: Message length, in bytes, forward to the CheckSum field. ALWAYS SECOND FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: CheckSum
Field.Description: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "Checksum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

Field.Name: ClOrdID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID (49) or OnBehalfOfCompID (5) as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

Field.Name: Commission
Field.Description: Commission. Note if CommType (3) is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

Field.Name: CommType
Field.Description: Commission type

Field.Name: CumQty
Field.Description: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Currency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values.

Field.Name: EndSeqNo
Field.Description: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo (7) = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

Field.Name: ExecID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of execution message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) for ExecType (50) =I (Order Status)). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day or the life of a multi-day order. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ExecID field to assure uniqueness across days. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ExecInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Field.Name: ExecRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with Trade Cancel and Trade Correct execution types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: HandlInst
Field.Description: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

Field.Name: SecurityIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID (48) value. Required if SecurityID is specified.

Field.Name: IOIID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of IOI message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQltyInd
Field.Description: Relative quality of indication

Field.Name: IOIRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: IOIQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

Field.Name: IOITransType
Field.Description: Identifies IOI message transaction type

Field.Name: LastCapacity
Field.Description: Broker capacity in order execution

Field.Name: LastMkt
Field.Description: Market of execution for last fill, or an indication of the market where an order was routed Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: LastPx
Field.Description: Price of this (last) fill.

Field.Name: LastQty
Field.Description: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoLinesOfText
Field.Description: Identifies number of lines of text body

Field.Name: MsgSeqNum
Field.Description: Integer message sequence number

Field.Name: MsgType
Field.Description: Defines message type ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted) Note: A "U" as the first character in the MsgType field (i.e. U, U2, etc) indicates that the message format is privately defined between the sender and receiver.

Field.Name: NewSeqNo
Field.Description: New sequence number

Field.Name: OrderID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: OrderQty
Field.Description: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or par, face or nominal value for FI instruments. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OrdStatus
Field.Description: Identifies current status of order. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrdType
Field.Description: Order type *** SOME VALUES ARE NO LONGER USED - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrigClOrdID
Field.Description: ClOrdID () of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

Field.Name: OrigTime
Field.Description: Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))

Field.Name: PossDupFlag
Field.Description: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

Field.Name: Price
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: RefSeqNum
Field.Description: Reference message sequence number

Field.Name: SecurityID
Field.Description: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource (22) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource.

Field.Name: SenderCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

Field.Name: SenderSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

Field.Name: SendingTime
Field.Description: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Quantity
Field.Description: Overall/total quantity (e.g. number of shares) (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: Side
Field.Description: Side of order

Field.Name: Symbol
Field.Description: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID (48) value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles) Use "[N/A]" for products which do not have a symbol.

Field.Name: TargetCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

Field.Name: TargetSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

Field.Name: Text
Field.Description: Free format text string (Note: this field does not have a specified maximum length)

Field.Name: TimeInForce
Field.Description: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY.

Field.Name: TransactTime
Field.Description: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: Urgency
Field.Description: Urgency flag

Field.Name: ValidUntilTime
Field.Description: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: SettlType
Field.Description: Indicates order settlement period. If present, SettlDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlType (63) and SettDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlType (63) is 0 (Regular) Regular is defined as the default settlement period for the particular security on the exchange of execution. In Fixed Income the contents of this field may influence the instrument definition if the SecurityID (48) is ambiguous. In the US an active Treasury offering may be re-opened, and for a time one CUSIP will apply to both the current and "when-issued" securities. Supplying a value of "7" clarifies the instrument description; any other value or the absence of this field should cause the respondent to default to the active issue.

Field.Name: SettlDate
Field.Description: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format. If present, this field overrides SettlType (63). This field is required if the value of SettlType (63) is 6 (Future) or 8 (Sellers Option). This field must be omitted if the value of SettlType (63) is 7 (When and If Issued) (expressed in local time at place of settlement)

Field.Name: SymbolSfx
Field.Description: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (67). Valid values: As defined in the NYSE Stock and bond Symbol Directory and in the AMEX Fitch Directory Fixed Income use: WI = "When Issued" for a security to be reissued under an old CUSIP or ISIN CD = a EUCP with lump-sum interest rather than discount price

Field.Name: ListID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

Field.Name: ListSeqNo
Field.Description: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrders (68), 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

Field.Name: TotNoOrders
Field.Description: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders (73) in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was named "ListNoOrds")

Field.Name: ListExecInst
Field.Description: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

Field.Name: AllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for allocation message. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: AllocTransType
Field.Description: Identifies allocation transaction type *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: RefAllocID
Field.Description: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (7) =Replace or Cancel. (Prior to FIX 4.1 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoOrders
Field.Description: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

Field.Name: AvgPxPrecision
Field.Description: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

Field.Name: TradeDate
Field.Description: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

Field.Name: PositionEffect
Field.Description: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

Field.Name: NoAllocs
Field.Description: Number of repeating AllocAccount (79)/AllocPrice (366) entries.

Field.Name: AllocAccount
Field.Description: Sub-account mnemonic

Field.Name: AllocQty
Field.Description: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: ProcessCode
Field.Description: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) /AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode instance indicates regular trade.

Field.Name: NoRpts
Field.Description: Total number of reports within series.

Field.Name: RptSeq
Field.Description: Sequence number of message within report series.

Field.Name: CxlQty
Field.Description: Total quantity canceled for this order. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoDlvyInst
Field.Description: Number of delivery instruction fields in repeating group. Note this field was removed in FIX 4.1 and reinstated in FIX 4.4.

Field.Name: AllocStatus
Field.Description: Identifies status of allocation

Field.Name: AllocRejCode
Field.Description: Identifies reason for rejection

Field.Name: Signature
Field.Description: Electronic signature

Field.Name: SecureDataLen
Field.Description: Length of encrypted message

Field.Name: SecureData
Field.Description: Actual encrypted data stream

Field.Name: SignatureLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in signature field.

Field.Name: EmailType
Field.Description: Email message type

Field.Name: RawDataLength
Field.Description: Number of bytes in raw data field.

Field.Name: RawData
Field.Description: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

Field.Name: PossResend
Field.Description: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

Field.Name: EncryptMethod
Field.Description: Method of encryption

Field.Name: StopPx
Field.Description: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

Field.Name: ExDestination
Field.Description: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: CxlRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection

Field.Name: OrdRejReason
Field.Description: Code to identify reason for order rejection.

Field.Name: IOIQualifier
Field.Description: Code to qualify IOI use

Field.Name: Issuer
Field.Description: Name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines, GNMA). see also Volume 7: "PRODUCT: FIXED INCOME - Euro Issuer Values"

Field.Name: SecurityDesc
Field.Description: Security description.

Field.Name: HeartBtInt
Field.Description: Heartbeat interval (seconds)

Field.Name: MinQty
Field.Description: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: MaxFloor
Field.Description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown on the exchange floor at any given time. (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: TestReqID
Field.Description: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

Field.Name: ReportToExch
Field.Description: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

Field.Name: LocateReqd
Field.Description: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: QuoteID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote

Field.Name: NetMoney
Field.Description: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

Field.Name: SettlCurrAmt
Field.Description: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

Field.Name: SettlCurrency
Field.Description: Currency code of settlement denomination.

Field.Name: ForexReq
Field.Description: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

Field.Name: OrigSendingTime
Field.Description: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

Field.Name: GapFillFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

Field.Name: NoExecs
Field.Description: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

Field.Name: ExpireTime
Field.Description: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") The meaning of expiration is specific to the context where the field is used. For orders, this is the expiration time of a Good Til Date TimeInForce. For Quotes - this is the expiration of the quote. Expiration time is provided across the quote message dialog to control the length of time of the overall quoting process. For collateral requests, this is the time by which collateral must be assigned. For collateral assignments, this is the time by which a response to the assignment is expected.

Field.Name: DKReason
Field.Description: Reason for execution rejection

Field.Name: DeliverToCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

Field.Name: DeliverToSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

Field.Name: IOINaturalFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

Field.Name: QuoteReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for quote request

Field.Name: BidPx
Field.Description: Bid price/rate

Field.Name: OfferPx
Field.Description: Offer price/rate

Field.Name: BidSize
Field.Description: Quantity of bid (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: OfferSize
Field.Description: Quantity of offer (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: NoMiscFees
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

Field.Name: MiscFeeAmt
Field.Description: Miscellaneous fee value

Field.Name: MiscFeeCurr
Field.Description: Currency of miscellaneous fee

Field.Name: MiscFeeType
Field.Description: Indicates type of miscellaneous fee

Field.Name: PrevClosePx
Field.Description: Previous closing price of security.

Field.Name: ResetSeqNumFlag
Field.Description: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

Field.Name: SenderLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: TargetLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

Field.Name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: DeliverToLocationID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient’s location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

Field.Name: NoRelatedSym
Field.Description: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

Field.Name: Subject
Field.Description: The subject of an Email message

Field.Name: Headline
Field.Description: The headline of a News message

Field.Name: URLLink
Field.Description: A URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) or URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://www.XYZ.com/research.html) See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards"

Field.Name: ExecType
Field.Description: Describes the specific ExecutionRpt (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus (39) will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: LeavesQty
Field.Description: Quantity open for further execution. If the OrdStatus (39) is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty (38) – CumQty (4). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: CashOrderQty
Field.Description: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as tradeable units (e.g. number of shares). The broker or fund manager (for CIV orders) would be responsible for converting and calculating a tradeable unit (e.g. share) quantity (OrderQty (38)) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

Field.Name: AllocAvgPx
Field.Description: AvgPx (6) for a specific AllocAccount (79) For Fixed Income this is always expressed as "percent of par" price type.

Field.Name: AllocNetMoney
Field.Description: NetMoney (8) for a specific AllocAccount (79)

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRate
Field.Description: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt (9) from Currency (5) to SettlCurrency (20)

Field.Name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
Field.Description: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate (55) should be multiplied or divided

Field.Name: NumDaysInterest
Field.Description: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income. Note value may be negative.

Field.Name: AccruedInterestRate
Field.Description: The amount the buyer compensates the seller for the portion of the next coupon interest payment the seller has earned but will not receive from the issuer because the issuer will send the next coupon payment to the buyer. Accrued Interest Rate is the annualized Accrued Interest amount divided by the purchase price of the bond.

Field.Name: AccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: SettlInstMode
Field.Description: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions message. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

Field.Name: AllocText
Field.Description: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount (79).

Field.Name: SettlInstID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for Settlement Instruction.

Field.Name: SettlInstTransType
Field.Description: Settlement Instructions message transaction type

Field.Name: EmailThreadID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

Field.Name: SettlInstSource
Field.Description: Indicates source of Settlement Instructions

Field.Name: SecurityType
Field.Description: Indicates type of security. See also the Product (460) and CFICode (46) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType for non-Fixed Income instruments. Example values (grouped by Product field value) (Note: additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties): * Identify the Issuer in the "Issuer" field(06) *** REPLACED values - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** NOTE: Additional values may be used by mutual agreement of the counterparties)

Field.Name: EffectiveTime
Field.Description: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: StandInstDbType
Field.Description: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

Field.Name: StandInstDbName
Field.Description: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (69) (i.e. the Global Custodian’s name).

Field.Name: StandInstDbID
Field.Description: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

Field.Name: SettlDeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: BidSpotRate
Field.Description: Bid F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: BidForwardPoints
Field.Description: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OfferSpotRate
Field.Description: Offer F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: OfferForwardPoints
Field.Description: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

Field.Name: OrderQty2
Field.Description: OrderQty (38) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: SettlDate2
Field.Description: SettDate (64) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

Field.Name: LastSpotRate
Field.Description: F/X spot rate.

Field.Name: LastForwardPoints
Field.Description: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate (94). May be a negative value.

Field.Name: AllocLinkID
Field.Description: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID (70)) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

Field.Name: AllocLinkType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID (96) is used.

Field.Name: SecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID (37) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: NoIOIQualifiers
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifiers (04).

Field.Name: MaturityMonthYear
Field.Description: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate (54) field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options). Format: YYYYMM (i.e. 199903) YYYYMMDD (20030323) YYYYMMwN (200303w) for week A specific date or can be appended to the MaturityMonthYear. For instance, if multiple standard products exist that mature in the same Year and Month, but actually mature at a different time, a value can be appended, such as "w" or "w2" to indicate week as opposed to week 2 expiration. Likewise, the date (0-3) can be appended to indicate a specific expiration (maturity date).

Field.Name: PutOrCall
Field.Description: Indicates whether an Option is for a put or call

Field.Name: StrikePrice
Field.Description: Strike Price for an Option.

Field.Name: CoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: Used for derivative products, such as options

Field.Name: OptAttribute
Field.Description: Can be used for SecurityType (67) =OPT to identify a particular security. Valid values vary by SecurityExchange: *** REPLACED values - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** For Exchange: MONEP (Paris) L = Long (a.k.a. "American") S = Short (a.k.a. "European") For Exchanges: DTB (Frankfurt), HKSE (Hong Kong), and SOFFEX (Zurich) 0-9 = single digit "version" number assigned by exchange following capital adjustments (0=current, =prior, 2=prior to , etc).

Field.Name: SecurityExchange
Field.Description: Market used to help identify a security. Valid values: See "Appendix 6-C"

Field.Name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

Field.Name: AllocHandlInst
Field.Description: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation message should handle/process the account details

Field.Name: MaxShow
Field.Description: Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI). (Prior to FIX 4.2 this field was of type int)

Field.Name: PegOffsetValue
Field.Description: Amount (signed) added to the peg for a pegged order in the context of the PegOffsetType (836) (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type PriceOffset)

Field.Name: XmlDataLen
Field.Description: Length of the XmlData data block.

Field.Name: XmlData
Field.Description: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

Field.Name: SettlInstRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID (62) with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType (63) transaction types.

Field.Name: NoRoutingIDs
Field.Description: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID (27) and RoutingType (26) values. See Volume 3: "Pre-Trade Message Targeting/Routing"

Field.Name: RoutingType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of RoutingID (27) specified

Field.Name: RoutingID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

Field.Name: Spread
Field.Description: For Fixed Income. Either Swap Spread or Spread to Benchmark depending upon the order type. Spread to Benchmark: Basis points relative to a benchmark. To be expressed as "count of basis points" (vs. an absolute value). E.g. High Grade Corporate Bonds may express price as basis points relative to benchmark (the BenchmarkCurveName (22) field). Note: Basis points can be negative. Swap Spread: Target spread for a swap.

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
Field.Description: Identifies currency used for benchmark curve. See "Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes" for information on obtaining valid values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurveName
Field.Description: Name of benchmark curve.

Field.Name: BenchmarkCurvePoint
Field.Description: Point on benchmark curve. Free form values: e.g. "Y", "7Y", "INTERPOLATED". Sample values: M = combination of a number between 1-12 and a "M" for month Y = combination of number between 1-100 and a "Y" for year} 10Y-OLD = see above, then add "-OLD" when appropriate INTERPOLATED = the point is mathematically derived 2/2031 5 3/8 = the point is stated via a combination of maturity month / year and coupon See Fixed Income-specific documentation at http://www.fixprotocol.org for additional values. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: IssueDate

Field.Name: RepurchaseRate

Field.Name: Factor
Field.Description: For Fixed Income: Amorization Factor for deriving Current face from Original face for ABS or MBS securities, note the fraction may be greater than, equal to or less than . In TIPS securities this is the Inflation index. Qty * Factor * Price = Gross Trade Amount For Derivatives: Contract Value Factor by which price must be adjusted to determine the true nominal value of one futures/options contract. (Qty * Price) * Factor = Nominal Value (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

Field.Name: ExDate
Field.Description: The date when a distribution of interest is deducted from a securities assets or set aside for payment to bondholders. On the ex-date, the securities price drops by the amount of the distribution (plus or minus any market activity). (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

Field.Name: ContractMultiplier

Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc. In general quantities for all calsses should be expressed in the basic unit of the instrument, e.g. shares for equities, norminal or par amount for bonds, currency for foreign exchange. When quantity is expressed in contracts, e.g. financing transactions and bond trade reporting, ContractMutliplier should contain the number of units in one contract and can be omitted if the multiplier is the default amount for the instrument, i.e. 1,000 par of bonds, 1,000,000 par for financing transactions.

Field.Name: WtAverageLiquidity
Field.Description: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ExchangeForPhysical
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

Field.Name: OutMainCntryUIndex
Field.Description: Value of stocks in Currency

Field.Name: CrossPercent
Field.Description: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

Field.Name: ProgRptReqs
Field.Description: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports

Field.Name: ProgPeriodInterval
Field.Description: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means don’t send status.

Field.Name: IncTaxInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross

Field.Name: NumBidders
Field.Description: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

Field.Name: BidTradeType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of trade

Field.Name: BasisPxType
Field.Description: Code to represent the basis price type

Field.Name: NoBidComponents
Field.Description: Indicates the number of list entries.

Field.Name: Country
Field.Description: ISO Country Code in field

Field.Name: TotNoStrikes
Field.Description: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66). Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: PriceType
Field.Description: Code to represent the price type

Field.Name: DayOrderQty
Field.Description: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty – (CumQty (4) – DayCumQty (425))

Field.Name: DayCumQty
Field.Description: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Field.Name: DayAvgPx
Field.Description: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

Field.Name: GTBookingInst
Field.Description: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate

Field.Name: NoStrikes
Field.Description: Number of list strike price entries.

Field.Name: ListStatusType
Field.Description: Code to represent the status type

Field.Name: NetGrossInd
Field.Description: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross

Field.Name: ListOrderStatus
Field.Description: Code to represent the status of a list order

Field.Name: ExpireDate
Field.Description: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local market’s business practices

Field.Name: ListExecInstType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of ListExecInst (69)

Field.Name: CxlRejResponseTo
Field.Description: Identifies the type of request that a Cancel Reject is in response to

Field.Name: UnderlyingCouponRate
Field.Description: Underlying security’s CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
Field.Description: Underlying security’s ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (23) field for description

Field.Name: ContraTradeQty
Field.Description: Quantity traded with the ContraBroker (375).

Field.Name: ContraTradeTime
Field.Description: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375). (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

Field.Name: LiquidityNumSecurities
Field.Description: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

Field.Name: MultiLegReportingType
Field.Description: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securities, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

Field.Name: StrikeTime
Field.Description: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

Field.Name: ListStatusText
Field.Description: Free format text string related to List Status.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
Field.Description: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

Field.Name: EncodedListStatusText
Field.Description: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

Field.Name: PartyIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified. See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: PartyID
Field.Description: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452). See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: NetChgPrevDay
Field.Description: Net change from previous day’s closing price vs. last traded price.

Field.Name: PartyRole
Field.Description: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified. See "Appendix 6-G – Use of <Parties> Component Block"

Field.Name: NoPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole (452) entries

Field.Name: NoSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of SecurityAltID (455) entries.

Field.Name: SecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: SecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Number of UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) entries.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
Field.Description: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

Field.Name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID is specified. Valid values: Same valid values as the SecurityIDSource (22) field

Field.Name: Product
Field.Description: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (46) and SecurityType (67) fields.

Field.Name: CFICode
Field.Description: Indicates the type of security using ISO 0962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 0962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See "Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (67) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (67) for non-Fixed Income instruments. A subset of possible values applicable to FIX usage are identified in "Appendix 6-D CFICode Usage - ISO 0962 Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code)"

Field.Name: UnderlyingProduct
Field.Description: Underlying security’s Product. Valid values: see Product(460) field

Field.Name: UnderlyingCFICode
Field.Description: Underlying security’s CFICode. Valid values: see CFICode (46)field

Field.Name: TestMessageIndicator
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

Field.Name: BookingRefID
Field.Description: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

Field.Name: IndividualAllocID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

Field.Name: RoundingDirection
Field.Description: Specifies which direction to round For CIV – indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrdQty (52) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (56) are specified on an order. The default is for rounding to be at the discretion of the executing broker or fund manager. e.g. for an order specifying CashOrdQty or OrderPercent if the calculated number of shares/units was 325.76 and RoundingModulus (469) was 0 – "round down" would give 320 units, "round up" would give 330 units and "round to nearest" would give 320 units.

Field.Name: RoundingModulus
Field.Description: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required. i.e. 0 means round to a multiple of 0 units/shares; 0.5 means round to a multiple of 0.5 units/shares. The default, if RoundingDirection (468) is specified without RoundingModulus, is to round to a whole unit/share.

Field.Name: CountryOfIssue
Field.Description: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

Field.Name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

Field.Name: LocaleOfIssue
Field.Description: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to http://www.atmos.albany.edu/cgi/stagrep-cgi Reference the IATA city codes for values. Note IATA (International Air Transport Association) maintains the codes at www.iata.org.

Field.Name: NoRegistDtls
Field.Description: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: MailingDtls
Field.Description: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

Field.Name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
Field.Description: The ISO 366 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

Field.Name: PaymentRef
Field.Description: "Settlement Payment Reference" – A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

Field.Name: DistribPaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution. 13 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: CashDistribCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions– see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CommCurrency
Field.Description: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (2) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: CancellationRights
Field.Description: For CIV – A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies

Field.Name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
Field.Description: A one character code identifying Money laundering status

Field.Name: MailingInst
Field.Description: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

Field.Name: TransBkdTime
Field.Description: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

Field.Name: ExecPriceType
Field.Description: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (3) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point

Field.Name: ExecPriceAdjustment
Field.Description: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

Field.Name: DateOfBirth
Field.Description: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

Field.Name: TradeReportTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Trade Report message transaction type (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was of type char)

Field.Name: CardHolderName
Field.Description: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardNumber
Field.Description: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardExpDate
Field.Description: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: CardIssNum
Field.Description: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

Field.Name: PaymentMethod
Field.Description: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 16 through 998 are reserved for future use Values above 000 are available for use by private agreement among counterparties

Field.Name: RegistAcctType
Field.Description: For CIV – a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund manager’s account types is required.

Field.Name: Designation
Field.Description: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a broker’s nominee or street name.

Field.Name: TaxAdvantageType
Field.Description: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonText
Field.Description: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

Field.Name: FundRenewWaiv
Field.Description: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentName
Field.Description: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentCode
Field.Description: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
Field.Description: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

Field.Name: CashDistribPayRef
Field.Description: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

Field.Name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
Field.Description: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

Field.Name: CardStartDate
Field.Description: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

Field.Name: PaymentDate
Field.Description: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

Field.Name: PaymentRemitterID
Field.Description: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

Field.Name: RegistStatus
Field.Description: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager

Field.Name: RegistRejReasonCode
Field.Description: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions has been rejected. The reason may be further amplified in the RegistRejReasonCode field. Possible values of reason code include:

Field.Name: RegistRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier for the RegistID (53) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (54) transaction types.

Field.Name: RegistDtls
Field.Description: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

Field.Name: NoDistribInsts
Field.Description: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions message

Field.Name: RegistEmail
Field.Description: Email address relating to Registration name and address details

Field.Name: DistribPercentage
Field.Description: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage

Field.Name: RegistID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

Field.Name: RegistTransType
Field.Description: Identifies Registration Instructions transaction type

Field.Name: ExecValuationPoint
Field.Description: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

Field.Name: OrderPercent
Field.Description: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investor’s total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investor’s cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

Field.Name: OwnershipType
Field.Description: The relationship between Registration parties.

Field.Name: NoContAmts
Field.Description: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report message

Field.Name: ContAmtType
Field.Description: Type of ContAmtValue (520). NOTE That Commission Amount / % in Contract Amounts is the commission actually charged, rather than the commission instructions given in Fields 2/3.

Field.Name: ContAmtValue
Field.Description: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (59).

Field.Name: ContAmtCurr
Field.Description: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see "Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes".

Field.Name: OwnerType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of owner

Field.Name: PartySubID
Field.Description: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452)=Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole=Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448), PartyIDSource (447), and PartyRole.

Field.Name: NestedPartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: NestedPartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: SecondaryClOrdID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: SecondaryExecID
Field.Description: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (7) used by an exchange or executing system.

Field.Name: OrderCapacity
Field.Description: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order (as of FIX 4.3, this field replaced Rule80A (tag 47) --used in conjunction with OrderRestrictions (529) field) (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

Field.Name: OrderRestrictions
Field.Description: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

Field.Name: MassCancelRequestType
Field.Description: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request

Field.Name: MassCancelResponse
Field.Description: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request

Field.Name: MassCancelRejectReason
Field.Description: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request was rejected

Field.Name: TotalAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Total number of orders affected by mass cancel request.

Field.Name: NoAffectedOrders
Field.Description: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

Field.Name: AffectedOrderID
Field.Description: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Field.Name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
Field.Description: SecondaryOrderID (98) of an order affected by a mass cancel request.

Field.Name: QuoteType
Field.Description: Identifies the type of quote. An indicative quote is used to inform a counterparty of a market. An indicative quote does not result directly in a trade. A tradeable quote is submitted to a market and will result directly in a trade against other orders and quotes in a market. A restricted tradeable quote is submitted to a market and within a certain restriction (possibly based upon price or quantity) will automatically trade against orders. Order that do not comply with restrictions are sent to the quote issuer who can choose to accept or decline the order. A counter quote is used in the negotiation model. See Volume 7 – Product: Fixed Income for example usage.

Field.Name: NestedPartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoNestedPartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of NestedPartyID (524), NestedPartyIDSource (525), and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

Field.Name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: *** DEPRECATED FIELD - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

Field.Name: MaturityDate
Field.Description: Date of maturity.

Field.Name: UnderlyingMaturityDate
Field.Description: Underlying security’s maturity date. See MaturityDate (54) field for description

Field.Name: InstrRegistry
Field.Description: The location at which records of ownership are maintained for this instrument, and at which ownership changes must be recorded.

Field.Name: CashMargin
Field.Description: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

Field.Name: NestedPartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: Scope
Field.Description: Defines the scope of a data element

Field.Name: MDImplicitDelete
Field.Description: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

Field.Name: CrossID
Field.Description: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

Field.Name: CrossType
Field.Description: Type of cross being submitted to a market

Field.Name: CrossPrioritization
Field.Description: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized. The definition of prioritization is left to the market. In some markets prioritization means which side of the cross order is applied to the market first. In other markets – prioritization may mean that the prioritized side is fully executed (sometimes referred to as the side being protected).

Field.Name: OrigCrossID
Field.Description: CrossID of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Cancel and Cross Cancel/Replace Requests.

Field.Name: NoSides
Field.Description: Number of Side repeating group instances.

Field.Name: Username
Field.Description: Userid or username.

Field.Name: Password
Field.Description: Password or passphrase.

Field.Name: NoLegs
Field.Description: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

Field.Name: LegCurrency
Field.Description: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

Field.Name: TotNoSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Type messages are used to return results (Prior to FIX 4.4 this field was named TotalNumSecurityTypes)

Field.Name: NoSecurityTypes
Field.Description: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

Field.Name: SecurityListRequestType
Field.Description: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request

Field.Name: SecurityRequestResult
Field.Description: The results returned to a Security Request message

Field.Name: RoundLot
Field.Description: The trading lot size of a security

Field.Name: MinTradeVol
Field.Description: The minimum trading volume for a security

Field.Name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
Field.Description: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order

Field.Name: LegPositionEffect
Field.Description: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg See PositionEffect (77) field for description

Field.Name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
Field.Description: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg See CoveredOrUncovered (203) field for description

Field.Name: LegPrice
Field.Description: Price for leg of a multileg See Price (44) field for description

Field.Name: TradSesStatusRejReason
Field.Description: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request was rejected

Field.Name: TradeRequestID
Field.Description: Trade Capture Report Request ID

Field.Name: TradeRequestType
Field.Description: Type of Trade Capture Report

Field.Name: PreviouslyReported
Field.Description: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

Field.Name: TradeReportID
Field.Description: Unique identifier of trade capture report

Field.Name: TradeReportRefID
Field.Description: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

Field.Name: MatchStatus
Field.Description: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison

Field.Name: MatchType
Field.Description: The point in the matching process at which this trade was matched

Field.Name: OddLot
Field.Description: This trade is to be treated as an odd lot

Field.Name: NoClearingInstructions
Field.Description: Number of clearing instructions

Field.Name: ClearingInstruction
Field.Description: Eligibility of this trade for clearing and central counterparty processing

Field.Name: TradeInputSource
Field.Description: Type of input device or system from which the trade was entered.

Field.Name: TradeInputDevice
Field.Description: Specific device number, terminal number or station where trade was entered

Field.Name: NoDates
Field.Description: Number of Date fields provided in date range

Field.Name: AccountType
Field.Description: Type of account associated with an order

Field.Name: CustOrderCapacity
Field.Description: Capacity of customer placing the order Primarily used by futures exchanges to indicate the CTICode (customer type indicator) as required by the US CFTC (Commodity Futures Trading Commission).

Field.Name: ClOrdLinkID
Field.Description: Permits order originators to tie together groups of orders in which trades resulting from orders are associated for a specific purpose, for example the calculation of average execution price for a customer or to associate lists submitted to a broker as waves of a larger program trade.

Field.Name: MassStatusReqID
Field.Description: Value assigned by issuer of Mass Status Request to uniquely identify the request

Field.Name: MassStatusReqType
Field.Description: Mass Status Request Type

Field.Name: OrigOrdModTime
Field.Description: The most recent (or current) modification TransactTime (tag 60) reported on an Execution Report for the order. The OrigOrdModTime is provided as an optional field on Order Cancel Request and Order Cancel Replace Requests to identify that the state of the order has not changed since the request was issued. This is provided to support markets similar to Eurex and A/C/E.

Field.Name: LegSettlType
Field.Description: Refer to values for SettlType[63]

Field.Name: LegSettlDate
Field.Description: Refer to description for SettlDate[64]

Field.Name: DayBookingInst
Field.Description: Indicates whether or not automatic booking can occur.

Field.Name: BookingUnit
Field.Description: Indicates what constitutes a bookable unit.

Field.Name: PreallocMethod
Field.Description: Indicates the method of preallocation.

Field.Description: Underlying security’s CountryOfIssue. See CountryOfIssue (470) field for description

Field.Name: UnderlyingStateOrProvinceOfIssue
Field.Description: Underlying security’s StateOrProvinceOfIssue. See StateOrProvinceOfIssue (471) field for description

Field.Description: Underlying security’s LocaleOfIssue. See LocaleOfIssue (472) field for description

Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityIDSource. See SecurityIDSource (22) field for description

Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltID. See SecurityAltID (455) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityAltIDSource
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityAltIDSource. See SecurityAltIDSource (456) field for description

Field.Name: LegProduct
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s Product. See Product (460) field for description

Field.Name: LegCFICode
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s CFICode. See CFICode (46) field for description

Field.Name: LegSecurityType
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s SecurityType. See SecurityType (67) field for description

Field.Name: LegMaturityMonthYear

Field.Name: LegMaturityDate
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s MaturityDate. See MaturityDate (54) field for description

Field.Name: LegStrikePrice
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s StrikePrice. See StrikePrice (202) field for description

Field.Name: LegOptAttribute
Field.Description: Multileg instrument's individual security’s OptAttribute. See OptAttribute (206) field for description

Field.Name: TradeReportType
Field.Description: Type of Trade Report

Field.Name: AllocNoOrdersType
Field.Description: Indicates how the orders being booked and allocated by an Allocation Instruction or Allocation Report message are identified, i.e. by explicit definition in the NoOrders group or not.

Field.Name: SharedCommission
Field.Description: Commission to be shared with a third party, e.g. as part of a directed brokerage commission sharing arrangement.

Field.Name: ConfirmReqID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a Confirmation Request message

Field.Name: AvgParPx
Field.Description: Used to express average price as percent of par (used where AvgPx field is expressed in some other way)

Field.Name: ReportedPx
Field.Description: Reported price (used to differentiate from AvgPx on a confirmation of a marked-up or marked-down principal trade)

Field.Name: NoCapacities
Field.Description: Number of repeating OrderCapacity entries.

Field.Name: OrderCapacityQty
Field.Description: Quantity executed under a specific OrderCapacity (e.g. quantity executed as agent, quantity executed as principal)

Field.Name: NoEvents
Field.Description: Number of repeating EventType entries.

Field.Name: EventType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of event

Field.Name: EventDate
Field.Description: Date of event

Field.Name: EventPx
Field.Description: Predetermined price of issue at event, if applicable

Field.Name: EventText
Field.Description: Comments related to the event.

Field.Name: PctAtRisk
Field.Description: Percent at risk due to lowest possible call.

Field.Name: NoInstrAttrib
Field.Description: Number of repeating InstrAttribType entries.

Field.Name: InstrAttribType
Field.Description: Code to represent the type of instrument attribute

Field.Name: InstrAttribValue
Field.Description: Attribute value appropriate to the InstrAttribType (87) field.

Field.Name: DatedDate
Field.Description: The effective date of a new securities issue determined by its underwriters. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Interest Accrual Date

Field.Name: InterestAccrualDate
Field.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date

Field.Name: CPProgram
Field.Description: The program under which a commercial paper is issued

Field.Name: CPRegType
Field.Description: The registration type of a commercial paper issuance

Field.Name: UnderlyingCPProgram
Field.Description: The program under which the underlying commercial paper is issued

Field.Name: UnderlyingCPRegType
Field.Description: The registration type of the underlying commercial paper issuance

Field.Name: UnderlyingQty
Field.Description: Unit amount of the underlying security (par, shares, currency, etc.)

Field.Name: TrdMatchID
Field.Description: Identifier assigned to a trade by a matching system.

Field.Name: SecondaryTradeReportRefID
Field.Description: Used to refer to a previous SecondaryTradeReportRefID when amending the transaction (cancel, replace, release, or reversal).

Field.Name: UnderlyingDirtyPrice
Field.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket. "Dirty" means it includes accrued interest

Field.Name: UnderlyingEndPrice
Field.Description: Price (percent-of-par or per unit) of the underlying security or basket at the end of the agreement.

Field.Name: UnderlyingStartValue
Field.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the start of the agreement

Field.Name: UnderlyingCurrentValue
Field.Description: Currency value currently attributed to this collateral

Field.Name: UnderlyingEndValue
Field.Description: Currency value attributed to this collateral at the end of the agreement

Field.Name: NoUnderlyingStips
Field.Description: Number of underlying stipulation entries

Field.Name: UnderlyingStipType
Field.Description: Type of stipulation. Same values as StipulationType (233)

Field.Name: UnderlyingStipValue
Field.Description: Value of stipulation. Same values as StipulationValue (234)

Field.Name: MaturityNetMoney
Field.Description: Net Money at maturity if Zero Coupon and maturity value is different from par value

Field.Name: MiscFeeBasis
Field.Description: Defines the unit for a miscellaneous fee.

Field.Name: TotNoAllocs
Field.Description: Total number of NoAlloc entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoAllocs in each message that has repeating NoAlloc entries related to the same AllocID or AllocReportID. Used to support fragmentation.

Field.Name: LastFragment
Field.Description: Indicates whether this message is the last in a sequence of messages for those messages that support fragmentation, such as Allocation Instruction, Mass Quote, Security List, Derivative Security List

Field.Name: CollReqID
Field.Description: Collateral Request Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnReason
Field.Description: Reason for Collateral Assignment

Field.Name: CollInquiryQualifier
Field.Description: Collateral inquiry qualifiers:

Field.Name: NoTrades
Field.Description: Number of trades in repeating group.

Field.Name: MarginRatio
Field.Description: The fraction of the cash consideration that must be collateralized, expressed as a percent. A MarginRatio of 02% indicates that the value of the collateral (after deducting for "haircut") must exceed the cash consideration by 2%.

Field.Name: MarginExcess
Field.Description: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

Field.Name: TotalNetValue
Field.Description: TotalNetValue is determined as follows: At the initial collateral assignment TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingStartValue * (1-haircut)). In a collateral substitution TotalNetValue is the sum of (UnderlyingCurrentValue * (1-haircut)). For listed derivatives clearing margin management, this is the collateral value which equals (Market value * haircut)

Field.Name: CashOutstanding
Field.Description: Starting consideration less repayments

Field.Name: CollAsgnID
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnTransType
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Transaction Type

Field.Name: CollRespID
Field.Description: Collateral Response Identifier

Field.Name: CollAsgnRespType
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Response Type

Field.Name: CollAsgnRejectReason
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Reject Reason

Field.Name: CollAsgnRefID
Field.Description: Collateral Assignment Identifier to which a transaction refers

Field.Name: CollRptID
Field.Description: Collateral Report Identifier

Field.Name: CollInquiryID
Field.Description: Collateral Inquiry Identifier

Field.Name: CollStatus
Field.Description: Collateral Status

Field.Name: TotNumReports
Field.Description: Total number or reports returned in response to a request

Field.Name: LastRptRequested
Field.Description: Indicates whether this message is that last report message in response to a request, such as Order Mass Status Request.

Field.Name: AgreementDesc
Field.Description: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction.

Field.Name: AgreementID
Field.Description: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

Field.Name: AgreementDate
Field.Description: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID and AgreementDesc was executed.

Field.Name: StartDate
Field.Description: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral

Field.Name: EndDate
Field.Description: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral

Field.Name: AgreementCurrency
Field.Description: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

Field.Name: DeliveryType
Field.Description: Identifies type of settlement

Field.Name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
Field.Description: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

Field.Name: StartCash
Field.Description: Starting dirty cash consideration of a financing deal, i.e. paid to the seller on the Start Date.

Field.Name: EndCash
Field.Description: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

Field.Name: UserRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a User Request.

Field.Name: UserRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the action required by a User Request Message

Field.Name: NewPassword
Field.Description: New Password or passphrase

Field.Name: UserStatus
Field.Description: Indicates the status of a user

Field.Name: UserStatusText
Field.Description: A text description associated with a user status.

Field.Name: StatusValue
Field.Description: Indicates the status of a network connection

Field.Name: StatusText
Field.Description: A text description associated with a network status.

Field.Name: RefCompID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

Field.Name: RefSubID
Field.Description: Assigned value used to identify specific elements within a firm.

Field.Name: NetworkResponseID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a network response.

Field.Name: NetworkRequestID
Field.Description: Unique identifier for a network resquest.

Field.Name: LastNetworkResponseID
Field.Description: Identifier of the previous Network Response message sent to a counterparty, used to allow incremental updates.

Field.Name: NetworkRequestType
Field.Description: Indicates the type and level of details required for a Network Status Request Message Boolean logic applies EG If you want to subscribe for changes to certain id’s then UserRequestType =0 (8+2), Snapshot for certain ID’s = 9 (8+)

Field.Name: NoCompIDs
Field.Description: Number of CompID entries in a repeating group.

Field.Name: NetworkStatusResponseType
Field.Description: Indicates the type of Network Response Message

Field.Name: NoCollInquiryQualifier
Field.Description: Number of CollInquiryQualifier entries in a repeating group.

Field.Name: TrdRptStatus
Field.Description: Trade Report Status

Field.Name: AffirmStatus
Field.Description: Identifies the status of the ConfirmationAck

Field.Name: UnderlyingStrikeCurrency
Field.Description: Currency in which the strike price of an underlying instrument is denominated

Field.Name: LegStrikeCurrency
Field.Description: Currency in which the strike price of a instrument leg of a multileg instrument is denominated

Field.Name: TimeBracket
Field.Description: A code that represents a time interval in which a fill or trade occurred. Required for US futures markets.

Field.Name: CollAction
Field.Description: Action proposed for an Underlying Instrument instance

Field.Name: CollInquiryStatus
Field.Description: Status of Collateral Inquiry

Field.Name: CollInquiryResult
Field.Description: Result returned in response to Collateral Inquiry 4000+ Reserved and available for bi-laterally agreed upon user-defined values

Field.Name: StrikeCurrency
Field.Description: Currency in which the StrikePrice is denominated.

Field.Name: NoNested3PartyIDs
Field.Description: Number of Nested3PartyID (949), Nested3PartyIDSource (950), and Nested3PartyRole (95) entries

Field.Name: Nested3PartyID
Field.Description: PartyID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448)

Field.Name: Nested3PartyIDSource
Field.Description: PartyIDSource value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyIDSource (447)

Field.Name: Nested3PartyRole
Field.Description: PartyRole value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartyRole (452)

Field.Name: NoNested3PartySubIDs
Field.Description: Number of Nested3PartySubIDs (953) entries

Field.Name: Nested3PartySubID
Field.Description: PartySubID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubID (523)

Field.Name: Nested3PartySubIDType
Field.Description: PartySubIDType value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

Field.Name: LegContractSettlMonth
Field.Description: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

Field.Name: LegInterestAccrualDate
Field.Description: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the Issue Date and the Dated Date
